This framework is public governance infrastructure. It was developed
to demonstrate that non-cognitive constraint enforcement, checkpoint-
based governance, and AI provider plurality can be implemented,
tested, and independently verified. It supports policy arguments
for mandatory AI governance accountability structures.

The author is not a technology company. This is not a product.
This is evidence that the architecture works.
